summary: In a series of stunning performances at the Monaco Diamond League, several world records fell. Faith Kipyegon shattered the 1500m record with a time of 3:49.04, while Jess Hull followed suit by breaking the 2000m record with an impressive 5:19.70. Hull's performance also marked the fifth fastest 1500m time in history. The Australian athlete's world record run in the 2000m has been hailed as one of Australia's greatest ever performances, with experts predicting that she could break an Olympic drought in the upcoming Games. The athletic world has been left in awe of Hull's accomplishments, labeling her performance as "insanity."

summary: Serena Williams made headlines after calling out NFL kicker Harrison Butker at the ESPYs, stating "We don't need you." Williams' comments sparked a social media uproar, with many supporting her stance and others criticizing her for using the platform to address political issues. Butker responded by emphasizing the unifying role of sports and expressing disappointment that Williams had "disinvited" those with differing opinions. The controversy has generated widespread discussion about inclusivity in sports and the use of public platforms to address social issues.

name: Ron E Sparks
summary: Legendary Australian radio presenter Ron E Sparks, known for his iconic voice and beloved personality, passed away at age 72. Colleagues and fans alike mourn the loss of this industry icon. Sparks had a long and illustrious career in the radio industry, presenting on WSFM and other prominent stations. Despite being diagnosed with a rare and aggressive form of cancer in 2021, Sparks continued to inspire and entertain his audience until his passing. His colleagues paid tribute to his exceptional talent, dedication to journalism, and unwavering spirit in the face of adversity.

name: Riley Thilthorpe
summary: Adelaide Crows rising star Riley Thilthorpe, who recently returned from injury, was forced to miss the team song after a post-match running session. Despite Thilthorpe's setback, the Crows remain optimistic about his recovery and believe he will make a significant contribution to the team going forward. The Crows secured a victory over the St Kilda Saints in a rain-soaked clash, with Thilthorpe featuring in the comeback. The match was marked by a penalty against Dockers skipper Nat Fyfe for high contact, while the Crows expressed confidence that their injured player Rankine remains a contender for All-Australian selection despite a suspension. The victory for the Crows comes amid a rebuilding phase, as they push aside the Saints in a gritty wet-weather affair. Meanwhile, St Kilda coach Ross Lyon vented his frustration by smashing his phone in anger, blaming the Adelaide Oval for the incident.
